% Capture-avoiding substitution test (spec 1.6.3).
% The notation body `Y\ cnst (F Y)` binds `Y` internally. The second
% fact passes an argument `(Z\ Y)` whose free variable `Y` collides
% with that binder. Without capture-avoidance, the outer `Y` would be
% captured by the body's binder and the rule body `Y = 8` could not
% propagate to the head -- the query below would fail. The capture-
% avoiding implementation alpha-renames the body binder so the outer
% `Y` remains free, the constraint `Y = 8` reaches the head, and the
% query succeeds.
kind myt type.
type cnst (nat -> myt).
notation lift F := Y\ cnst (F Y).
type p ((nat -> myt) -> o).
p (lift (Z\ Z)).
p (lift (Z\ Y)) :- Y = 8.
